===== AeroDyn v15 Input File ==========================================================
DTU 10MW onshore reference wind turbine v0.1 - OpenFAST v3.5.3
===== General Options =================================================================
               FALSE   Echo           - Echo the input to <RootName>.AD.ech (flag)
           "default"   DTAero         - Time interval for aerodynamic calculations (s)
                   1   WakeMod        - Type of wake/induction model (0=none, 1=BEMT, 2=DBEMT)
                   1   AFAeroMod      - Type of blade airfoil aerodynamics model (1=steady model, 2=Beddoes-Leishman unsteady model)
                   0   TwrPotent      - Type tower influence on wind based on potential flow around the tower (0=none, 1=baseline potential flow, 2=potential flow with Bak correction)
                   0   TwrShadow      - Calculate tower influence on wind based on downstream tower shadow (flag)
               FALSE   TwrAero        - Calculate tower aerodynamic loads (flag)
               FALSE   FrozenWake     - Assume frozen wake during linearization (flag)
               FALSE   CavitCheck     - Perform cavitation check (flag)
               FALSE   Buoyancy       - Include buoyancy effects (flag)
               FALSE   CompAA         - Flag to compute AeroAcoustics calculation
            "unused"   AA_InputFile   - Aeroacoustics input file
===== Environmental Conditions ========================================================
               1.225   AirDens        - Air density (kg/m^3)
           1.784E-05   KinVisc        - Kinematic air viscosity (m^2/s)
              337.29   SpdSound       - Speed of sound (m/s)
            101325.0   Patm           - Atmospheric pressure (Pa)
              1700.0   Pvap           - Vapour pressure of fluid (Pa)
===== Blade-Element/Momentum Theory Options ===========================================
                   1   SkewMod        - Type of skewed-wake correction model (1=uncoupled, 2=Pitt/Peters, 3=coupled)
           "default"   SkewModFactor  - Constant used in Pitt/Peters skewed wake model (15/32*pi)
               FALSE   TipLoss        - Use the Prandtl tip-loss model
               FALSE   HubLoss        - Use the Prandtl hub-loss model
               FALSE   TanInd         - Include tangential induction in BEMT calculations
               FALSE   AIDrag         - Include the drag term in the axial-induction calculation
               FALSE   TIDrag         - Include the drag term in the tangential-induction calculation
           "Default"   IndToler       - Convergence tolerance for BEMT nonlinear solve residual equation
                 200   MaxIter        - Maximum number of iteration steps
===== Dynamic Blade-Element/Momentum Theory Options ===================================
                   2   DBEMT_Mod      - Type of dynamic BEMT (DBEMT) model (1=constant tau1, 2=time-dependent tau1)
                 4.0   tau1_const     - Time constant for DBEMT (s)
===== OLAF -- cOnvecting LAgrangian Filaments (Free Vortex Wake) Theory Options =======
            "unused"   OLAFInputFileName - Input file for OLAF
===== Beddoes-Leishman Unsteady Airfoil Aerodynamics Options ==========================
                   1   UAMod          - Unsteady Aero Model Switch (1=Baseline model (Original), 2=Gonzalez's variant, 3=Minemma/Pierce variant)
                TRUE   FLookup        - Flag for f' lookup or best-fit exponential equations
===== Airfoil Information =============================================================
                   1   AFTabMod       - Interpolation method for multiple airfoil tables
                   1   InCol_Alfa     - The column in the airfoil tables that contains the angle of attack
                   2   InCol_Cl       - The column in the airfoil tables that contains the lift coefficient
                   3   InCol_Cd       - The column in the airfoil tables that contains the drag coefficient
                   4   InCol_Cm       - The column in the airfoil tables that contains the pitching-moment coefficient
                   0   InCol_Cpmin    - The column in the airfoil tables that contains the Cpmin coefficient
                   6   NumAFfiles     - Number of airfoil files used
